ext","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn by the Arabs of the desert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hibarap","text_ar":"حِبَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) so called because of the diversity of the colours of its stripes: (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"my^ozar","text_ar":"ميْزَر"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of those worn by the Arabs of the desert, that is a striped"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amolap","text_ar":"شَمْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAth:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a striped"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAr","text_ar":"اـِزَار"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wool;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nimaArN","text_ar":"نِمَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAth, Msb:) it is an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates. (TA.) It is said in a trad. of Saad,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaTiY~N fiY Hubowatihi A^aEoraAbY~N fiY namiratihi A^asadN fiY taA^omuwratihi","text_ar":"نَبَطِىٌّ فِى حُبْوَتِهِ اَعْرَابىٌّ فِى نَمِرَتِهِ اَسَدٌ فِى تَاْمُورَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A Nabathean in his hubweh"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a long piece of cloth, or the like, wound round the back and legs of a person sitting with his thighs against his belly);"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an Arab of the desert in his nemireh; a lion in his den"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anomaru","text_ar":"اَنْمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","M","A","Mgh","Msb","IAth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}